The paper deals with the combinatorial optimization problem of finding the minimum spanning tree on a complete graph, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The study of extensions of polytopes is a topic in computational complexity theory, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves the study of geometric objects such as polytopes and communication protocols, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of lower bounds and nondeterministic communication protocols suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT).
